<paragraph blockId="41.[178,401,548,570]" box="[178,401,548,570]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">
Female: 
<figureCitation box="[266,397,548,570]" captionStart="Figs 241-242" captionStartId="84.[178,218,1507,1527]" captionTargetBox="[189,1080,217,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-1@84.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="Figs 241-242: Mesa sahariana: (241) habitus; (242) basal hindtarsomerus; Figs 243-248: Mesa sahariana: (243) head and pronotum, dorsal aspect; (244) head, frontal aspect; (245) epipygium, dorsal aspect; (246) gonosquama;(247) volsella; (248) aedeagus; (241: scale bar: 2.5mm; 242: scale bar: 0.5 mm; 243-244: scale bar: 1mm; 245-248: scale bar: 0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303421" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303421/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">figs 241-242</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[178,1086,585,695]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">
Black. Metasoma is completely ferruginous but brown petiole. Wings hyaline. Calcaria and spines light yellowish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[460,502,614,636]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">cOc</emphasis>
complete on the upper side along vertex. Rounded edge between outer and anterior surfaces of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,630,643,667]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">
Es 
<subScript attach="left" box="[622,630,653,667]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
. ¾ epipygium wrinkled, with dense apical micro 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[237,251,673,695]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">p</emphasis>
. Gradulus present on 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[486,499,667,681]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">rd</superScript>
tergum, absent in 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[700,712,667,681]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">th</superScript>
one. Scopa: 
<figureCitation box="[843,925,673,695]" captionStart="Figs 241-242" captionStartId="84.[178,218,1507,1527]" captionTargetBox="[189,1080,217,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-1@84.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="Figs 241-242: Mesa sahariana: (241) habitus; (242) basal hindtarsomerus; Figs 243-248: Mesa sahariana: (243) head and pronotum, dorsal aspect; (244) head, frontal aspect; (245) epipygium, dorsal aspect; (246) gonosquama;(247) volsella; (248) aedeagus; (241: scale bar: 2.5mm; 242: scale bar: 0.5 mm; 243-244: scale bar: 1mm; 245-248: scale bar: 0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303421" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303421/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">fig. 242</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[178,701,710,732]" box="[178,701,710,732]" pageId="41" pageNumber="1698">
